The Telegraph - Calcutta : Sports

 Spiker in drugs net

OUR CORRESPONDENT

Bangalore: A state-level volleyball player from Madhya Pradesh and his accomplice have been arrested for possessing 5kg of heroin. 

Spiker Anjani Kumar Singh, 28, and Ehsan Bakshi, 52, were taken into custody following a tip-off. City Police Commissioner N. Achyut Rao said the recovered heroin was estimated to be worth Rs 6 crore. 

Singh and Bakshi were caught while trying to get into an autorickshaw on Thursday on Church Street, a popular youth hangout where many fashionable pubs, bars and restaurants are located. 




